You have such an interesting channel, Brad. The whole "let's play" concept was one that blew up heavily in the earlier years of YouTube gaming content. But eventually it kind of died out when other content became more heavily favored by the platform itself and other factors. Therefore, lots of people stopped doing let's play videos (Pewdiepie for example). But you, you didn't ever stop reusing the formula that you built your channel on and you are still by far an excellent and popular youtuber. I've heard lots of people talk about how if you want to be a youtuber, you have to adapt to what people want to watch. But it seems that what people want to watch isn't as consistent as most mainstream YouTubers believe. Just my thoughts.
